description: Dup. K 2574+ (BAM V 482 ii 27-33, see p. xxvi), medical. (+)K 6066+? Neo-Assyrian.

content.value: [If a man’s right temple causes him seizing pain and his right eye contains blood: you crush (and) sieve together @i{saḫlû}-cress, @i{ḫašû}-thyme, gypsum], @i{dadānu}-plant, [parched grain flour (and) malt porridge. You boil down (the mixture) in vinegar, DITTO].

content.value: [If] both of a man’s temples cause him seizing pain and both his eyes [contain blood]: you crush (and) sieve [@i{kukru}-aromatic, @i{burāšu}-juniper, parched grain flour] (and) dried sesame husk. [You mix it with coarse flour, you knead (the mixture) in beer, (and) you put it on as a bandage].

notes:
CRANIUM 2 ms. C [KS]
“ dup. K.2574+ (BAM V 482 II 27-33)… Teil der 2. Tafel (des Kapitels) @akk{DIŠ NA UGU-šu₂ KUM₂ u₂-kal} (das gleichzeitig übergordneter Titel des gesamten therapeutischen Werkes der Babylonier u. Assyrer ist, wie aus der Uruk-
Texten hervorgeht). Offenbar Teil des 3. Exemplars aus Ninive. Oder Sammeltafel?”
